data.text: @JosephFrankel @NYMag It was like a movie set of what a “college coffee shop” should look like. It was all wood & rustic art, “natural” & everything on the screens & walls was aggressively multicultural. Felt forced. My husband felt it 1st. He HATED it

@NYMag @JosephFrankel My husband & I wandered in off the street. It was very Stepford-y. I’m a prof so they let me order for him, but just this once, they said. That’s ok since we’re not going back, but we’re not their target anyway
@NYMag @JosephFrankel “Companies interested in hiring those students.” Uh-huh.
@NYMag @JosephFrankel Some day we’re going to learn that data, like equity, is not really free to give away...
